    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-10-19T19:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-10-19T19:16:00-05:00" n="697"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d697">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A322/10–1953: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 697<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Syria</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-10-19T19:16:00-05:00"
                            >October 19, 1953—7:16 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>143. Re <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 149<note n="1" xml:id="d697fn1"
                        >Not printed, but see <ref target="#d693fn6">footnote 6, Document
                        693</ref>.</note> Emb shld if necessary make abundantly clear to <persName
                        corresp="#p_ASGA1">Shishakli</persName> that incident similar Tel al-Mutilah
                    wld not embellish Syr case. Dept has backed fully <persName corresp="#p_BMGV1"
                        >Bennike</persName> decision, has withheld economic aid Israel. Finally, US
                    in concert with UK and France is spearheading Security Council examination
                    incidents. In return US hopes Syr will exercise all possible restraint and
                    permit Security Council reach decision without further complications.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
